## Quick context the next session might otherwise have to rediscover

- `polytoken --version` → `0.4.0-unstable.7`. `polytoken openapi` is the
  authoritative source (hosted changelog lags daily releases).
- `/prompt` now AUTO-QUEUES when busy (202 + `queued_item`), does NOT 409. 409
  = slash-while-busy or full queue only. Both drivers were collapsed onto this.
- SSE emits `heartbeat` ~10s (unstable.5+); liveness is a 30s timeout on
  `stream.next()` (3× cadence). SSE resume via `Last-Event-ID` is a known
  upstream NO-OP — the reconnect scenario asserts RESEED, not resume replay.
- The `parity/` harness lists sessions ONLY via `polytokenSessions()` (isolated
  `--sessions-dir`); never call bare `polytoken sessions` (it lists prod).
